merican actor  Jon Voight  (  b. 1938 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Jonathan","meanings":["Biblical name, meaning ‘God has given’, composed of the same elements as those of   Matthew  , but in reverse order. This is the name of several characters in the Bible, most notably a son of King Saul, who was a devoted friend and supporter of the young David, even when David and Saul were themselves at loggerheads (1 Samuel 31; 2 Samuel 1:19–26). The name is often taken as symbolic of steadfast friendship and loyalty. Well-known bearers of the name include the Irish clergyman and writer  Jonathan Swift  (  1667-1745 ), British theatre director  Jonathan Miller  (  b. 1934 ), British actor  Jonathan Pryce  (  b. 1947 ), and British television presenter  Jonathan Ross  (  b. 1960 )."]},{"name":"Jonn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jon   or  <b>John</b> ."]},{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]},{"name":"\"Lochlain\"","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Said to refer originally to a migrant from Norway, the ‘land of the lochs’ (  compare  <b>Lachlan</b>   )."],"variants":[{"name":"Laughlin","meanings":["Anglicized form of   Lochlainn ."]},{"name":"Loughlin","meanings":["Anglicized form of   Lochlainn   ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mac Con \"Lochlain\" MacNamara was born in 1319, in Ireland, his father, Cumedha MacNamara, was 49 and his mother, Mrs Macnamara, was 39. He married Hannah ODwyre in 1347, in Ireland. They were the parents of at least 4 sons."},"et":{"       1319–Deceased":"1319–Surnud","1319–Male":"1319–Surnud","1320–Female":"1320–Surnud","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","1349–1369":"1349–1369","1350–Male":"1350–Surnud","1358–1378":"1358–1378","1360–Male":"1360–Surnud","1368–Male":"1368–Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1280–Female":"1280–Surnud","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1360":"1360","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","13